### Updates

Attributes not marked as `(Updatable)` cannot be modified after resource creation. To change these attributes, the resource must be recreated.

## Import

This resource does not support import.

`ciphertrust_aws_key_rotation` represents a one-time key material rotation
request submitted to AWS for an existing native symmetric AWS key. Once the
request is sent, AWS processes the rotation asynchronously and there is no API
endpoint that returns the details of a past rotation in a form that matches this
resource's state.

Specifically:

- The `status` attribute is a locally generated timestamp message set by the
  provider at create time (for example, "A key material rotation request was
  sent to AWS on 2026-01-01 00:00:00 UTC."). It is not stored in or returned
  by CipherTrust Manager, so it cannot be reconstructed on import.
- The `id` attribute includes a random UUID suffix appended by the provider at
  create time. No API call can recover this value, so any imported resource
  would carry a different ID from the one that was originally created.

Importing this resource would leave `status` absent from state and cause a
permanent plan diff on every subsequent apply.

To view the rotation history of an AWS key, use the
`ciphertrust_aws_key_rotation_list` data source instead.
